EditorData.NodeContext: Consistent Crying/panic/fatigued. You are powerless and fearing for your life. The player only needs one strike to finish you.
Vocalization sounds when Falling into infinity(~0.5 - 2 sec)
Peaceful muttering with occasional snoring sounds when the character is asleep(~2-4 sec)
Vocalization sounds when Freezing to death(~0.5 - 2 sec)
A short burst of angry grunts and heavy breathing
A higher intensity grunt and some groaning as you recover from the impact

6 bespoke screams of growing intensity as each piece of the armor is destroyed.

Intensity 1: light scream; character is still confident.
Intensity 2: same as intensity 1, but with more anger and agitation
Intensity 3: an angry mdium-intensity scream
Intensity 4: same as intensity 3, but with pain mixed in
Intensity 5: high intensity scream, almost like your arm got chopped off
Intensity 6: highest possible intensity; character has no protection, no strength, nothing left - and is entering a state of desperation.
The cinematics intro has the Toll Collector smelling and sensing the players gold. Aggressive sniffing/inhaling like a drug dog and an exert of joy as you realize there is fresh gold nearby
Sounds of falling from a high place, Scared but not in a panic. (~2-4 sec)
aggressive grunts and exerts in aniticipation of wanting to hit someone
Combat begins.
A long painful scream as you deperately breath your last breath
Think stomach pains Like you go to your knee holding your stomach in pain. This vocalization will trigger on debuffs and negative statuses(~1-2 sec)
Open Mouth short strenuous effort.Short effort of jumping off a ledge pushing something heavy, trying to untangle oneself(~0.5-0.8 sec)

Feeling Stronger better, When an ally casts a helping spell on you, feeling more confident, protected, reassured. This will be cast on party members and only the enemies will cast it between themselves so we can really nail the feeling of Ah! “nothing can stop me now” a little laugh can really sell it (~1-2 sec)
Light effort grunt followed by a short burst of mocking laughter
light intensity grunt as as you get hit by a standard attackL
Character manically laughing, insane and uncontrollable
Vocalization sounds when burnt alive(~0.5 - 2 sec)
Character laughing, natural, joyful, Can have multiple variation on the type of laughter
Character that is getting healed or recovered. Relief of pain
A high intensity effort as if throwing something heavy
Some shout for when she summons her minions.
Celebratory laughter after killing the player
Closed Mouth short strenuous effort.Short effort of jumping off a ledge pushing something heavy, trying to untangle oneself(~0.5-0.8 sec)

A fatigued/discouraged attack sound when the character is weak and enters the 'desperate' state. A high effort grunt but with a hint of pain in it and discouraged. You're attacking the player in your weakest state. You are scared and have no power. your strike is as strong as a wet noodle.

A long and deep (about 3 seconds) inhumane inhale of desperation as if breathing in oxygen for the first time in a long time followed by a big sigh of relief. Imagine a drug addict inhaling fumes after a long withdrawal.  can happen multiple times in the cinematic so a few different variations would be nice
Aggressive grunts and exerts in aniticipation of wanting to hit someone
Vocalization sounds when attacking with extra force for a critical hit, this is when an attack had dealt extra damage because of chance! Explosive energy. Angrier performance.(~0.5-1.5 sec)
Vocalization sounds when Dying old age in an instant, Think about turning 250 years old in 1 sec Body experiences an accelerated withering effect. (~0.5 - 2 sec)
